alwaysApply: true
---

# This is critical guideline that must be followed whatever happens.
- NO unnecessary inline comments unless needed.
- Separation of concerns is a must (as example but not limited to):
    - Actions
    - Services
    - Repositories
- With concerns separated, there must be no fat controllers nor models.
- Always type hint parameters and return types.
- Always import classes do not use full namespaces.
- Use single name as much as possible. ASK FIRST if you cannot find suitable one.
    - Variables
    - Models
    - Classes
    - Attributes
    - etc.
- Always refer to @laravel-boost for implementation guide.